data.text:
TVMDL is accepting public comment on proposed fee changes for Fiscal Year 2025 until August 23.

To view these proposed changes, visit the FY25 Proposed Fee Changes page.

Starting April 29, the USDA requires lactating dairy cows to be tested for HPAI prior to movement.

View TVMDL’s guidelines to mitigate potential delays when submitting dairy samples for movement testing.

Cytologic evaluation of body fluid samples. Includes gross examination, total protein concentration, cell counts (where indicated and with EDTA and non-flocculent samples), preparation of direct, concentrated and cytocentrifuge slides (where indicated), and microscopic evaluation by a clinical pathologist.
